txt.en: Hógur is expecting this weapon shipment in Járnfast.\n\nYou should talk to Hógur.
Although many weapons were stolen by the Easterlings, Grámi Hornhelm has asked you to deliver what weapons they can spare to Járnfast.
The Hammerstead weapons have been crated and are ready for delivery.\n\nYou should collect the weapon crate.
The weapons are ready to be taken to Járnfast

'Since you are heading to Járnfast, please take this crate of weapons with you. They were expecting a much larger convoy, but all we have to spare now are the ones you successfully recovered from the Easterlings. And of course, the dagger you smithed yourself. It will have to do. Bring them to Hógur, one of Lord Náin's advisors.'
'This is all that is left after the Easterling attack? Lord Náin must act soon, before we are overwhelmed by these curs. Thank you for your assistance in this matter, [placeholder].'
